name: ThePirateBay - the transparent way
description:
Choose your favorite background and find your torrents on floating flakes of glass - go ahead, sail away!

A bunch of high quality wallpapers are offered as seen below (*)
Very easy to pick an another if you prefer, just browse your own collection on the harddrive, paste a web address, or follow the instructions below.
You can also change the text colors.
additional_info: Update Oct 21, 2017: (*) At the moment, I can't load TPB with wallpapers from this style anymore. I have no clue why because none of my other styles encounter this problem. As a result, you will get a blank (white) background and that looks awful to me. So I give you an option to pick your own background color (I have set it to black as default), in case those wallpaper don't work for you too. ------------------------------------------- How to replace the images (edit in the code) - this is not necessary, but it makes the page load much faster: If you find an image you would like to use, then download and save it to your HDD/SSD because the page will be loaded MUCH FASTER with an image from a disc than from a busy web address!! Especially on larger images. 1. So, find a nice wallpaper and download it to your computer. Let's assume in this example that you want to download the wallpaper called "Space Sunset" ( http://i.imgur.com/yndRntW.jpg ) and save it on the pathway d:\ 2. See line 10 in the code: --wallpaper: url("http://i.imgur.com/yndRntW.jpg") In this example you should change the pathway http ://i.imgur.com/ to file://d:/ where the d: (or c:, or e:, etc) is the letter of your disc/partition the image is stored on (remember to include the full eventual path way to your image). You should also write (or copy/paste) the title of your image (in the example the title is yndRntW.jpg ) Following this example, it can look like this: --wallpaper: url("file://d:/yndRntW.jpg") 3. Hit the "Preview" button to see how it looks. If you like it, then hit "Save" and you are done :) ------------------------------- Regarding adds, banners, popup's and other sh*t on TPB; I haven't found any script who's working - they are all useless because TPB probably use "Geotargeting" (meaning I can block all where I live, but you live somewhere else....). So, I haven't spent time on it because I know I also should fail... Best solution is to use the add-on AdBlock Plus and (important) use this subscription: Fanboy Ultimate Adblock list (it's a merge of the popular Fanboy and Easylist). With this subscription installed I have reached a 100% successful ad/popup-extinction, highly recommended!

/* AGENT_SHEET */ @namespace url(http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml);
@-moz-document domain("thepiratebay.se"), regexp('https?:\/\/(thepiratebay|pirateproxy|bayporn|suprbay|thevideobay|torrindex|thebootlegbay|themusicbay|superbay|tvbay|scenerelease|sharereactor)\..+') {
:root {   

/* Change WALLPAPER (BACKGROUND), and the PATHWAY to your wallpaper: */
     
              /* Example:  url(" http://webaddress.com/media/imagefile.jpg ") <=> replace    http://webaddress.com/media/   with    file://d:/   
                 =   wallpaper saved on harddrive named d:/imagefile.jpg  (or c:/, or whatever pathway you have to your saved wallpaper) */

     --wallpaper: url("/*[[yyy]]*/")  ;    
               
              
/* Change TEXT COLOR:

   The used colors (RGB-numbers, see example in the pictures) is 
        - WHITE: 255,255,255 
        - ORANGE: 255,153,0 
        - BLUE: 22,200,255 
        - TURQUOISE: 71,255,248 
        - RED: 255,0,0 
        - PINK: 255,193,193 
        - BLUEBERRY: 173,187,255
        - but feel free to use your own favorites... 

   As standard I have used these colors below, but it's your choice how many colors you want to combine: */     
      
     --1st-color: /*[[main]]*/ ;              /*   The main text color, standard is WHITE (255,255,255)                                                                       */
     --2nd-color: /*[[second]]*/ ;              /*   Hover color on links, standard is PINK (255,193,193)                                                                       */
     --3rd-color: /*[[third]]*/ ;              /*   Other "less important text" color (e.g. comments), standard is LIGHTGREY (211,211,211)                                     */
     --button-color: /*[[button]]*/ ;           /*   Button color, standard is BLUEBERRY (173,187,255,1)                                                                           */
     --buttact-color: /*[[buttact]]*/ ;     /*   On-click (actived) color on buttons, standard is BLUEBERRY (173,187,255) with transparency-level (opacity) of 67%           */
     --input-color: /*[[input]]*/ ;            /*   All input fields color (exept the searchbox) as e.g. login-forms and category-boxes, standard is BLUEBERRY (173,187,255)    */

     --title-color: /*[[title]]*/ ;            /*   The title color, standard is BLUEBERRY (173,187,255)                                                                        */ 
     --cursor-color: /*[[cursor]]*/ ;           /*   The text color on cursor, standard is PINK (255,193,193)                                                                    */
     --linehov-color: /*[[linehov]]*/ ;          /*   The hovered table search line color, standard is BLUEBERRY (173,187,255)                                                    */  

/* End change text color */

    --tpb-logo:
url(data:image/png;base64,)  }
